#1001
Ash-Veined Trail~
The trail threads between trunks whose @@bbark@@N has taken on a charcoal hue, each surface cross-hatched with pale veins of mineral-white ash that trace the wood's internal rot.  Clumps of grey-green lichen droop from the lower branches in long tattered streamers, brushing the shoulders of anyone who passes and leaving a faintly acrid residue.  The undergrowth on either side is dead but refuses to fall, dry stalks standing upright in a mockery of living foliage.~
0 3
D3
The trail leads back west toward the threshold of the Withered Depths.~
~
0 -1 1000
D1
The path bends east through increasingly distorted woodland.~
~
