#1002
Stand of Blackened Birches~
A cluster of birch trees stands here with their bark turned entirely black, the characteristic white peeling reduced to grey shreds that drift in the still air like flakes of dead skin.  The ground between them is carpeted with a dark, spongy mat of compressed leaves that squelch underfoot and release a sweet-rotten odour with every step.  Something has clawed deep furrows into the nearest trunk at shoulder height, the gouges still fresh enough to weep a thin amber sap.~
0 3
D0
The path leads north toward the darkened trailhead.~
~
0 -1 1000
D1
A game trail of sorts cuts east through the birch stand.~
~
0 -1 1004
D2
The ground slopes gently south, the birches giving way to denser growth.~
~
0 -1 1005
S
#1003
The Corrupted Crossroads~
Four routes meet here in a rough clearing where a long-dead signpost still stands, its wood so consumed by @@pfungal rot@@N that the carved lettering is entirely illegible.  The post leans at an angle, a crust of purple-tinged mushrooms climbing its base in neat concentric rings.  The trees at each compass point look different — each direction seems to pull the forest into a slightly distinct character of corruption, as though the blight has found multiple vocabularies to express its single, malignant idea.~
0 3
D3
The trail leads back west through the ash-veined stretch of path.~
