#1005
Rotting Undergrowth~
The forest floor here is almost entirely consumed by a thick mat of @@ddecomposing plant matter@@N, the original soil invisible beneath a knee-deep accumulation of mulched leaves and collapsed fungi.  Each footstep plunges through a crispy surface layer into something cold and wet beneath, releasing gouts of musty vapour that rise about the ankles.  Saplings that tried to push through the rot have been absorbed rather than nourished, their thin grey trunks bent sideways and slowly disappearing into the mat.~
