#1007
Fungus-Veined Forest Floor~
The ground here is alive, if alive is the right word, with an interlocking network of @@pfungal mycelium@@N spreading just beneath a translucent skin of compressed leaf litter.  The threads catch the faint ambient light and glow an eerie blue-purple, making the entire forest floor shimmer with cold bioluminescence that casts no warmth.  Standing still long enough, a faint vibration can be felt through the soles of the feet, as though the mycelium network carries a pulse of its own.~
