#1008
The Hollow Trunk Clearing~
A massive tree fell here long ago, and its hollow trunk now lies on its side, the interior colonised by a community of shelf fungi that have built a layered architecture of orange and brown brackets inside the rotting wood.  The clearing the fall created is long since overgrown, but the fallen trunk remains, slowly merging with the ground beneath it.  Dark stains streak the bark of the surrounding trees at a uniform height, as if something habitually rubs against them at that level when passing through.~
