#1009
The Stagnant Pool~
A shallow depression in the forest floor has collected a pool of standing water the colour of old tea, its surface covered in a floating mat of @@dblack algae@@N and drowned leaves.  No ripple crosses it; no insect skims it; nothing lives in it or on it.  The trees ringing the pool have sent roots directly into the water, and where the roots break the surface they are coated in a white crystalline deposit that might be salt, might be fungal spore, and is certainly something that should not be touched.~
