#1043
The Dense Thicket~
This section of the maze is the most compressed yet — the vines here have grown so tightly that the passage through them requires turning sideways, and thorns catch clothing and skin despite care.  The density creates a near-silence: the sounds from other parts of the maze — the scraping, the wind-breath — do not penetrate here.  What can be heard instead, with the external noise blocked, is something much closer: a slow pulse, rhythmic and organic, coming from the vines themselves, as though the bramble mass has a heartbeat.~
