The maze opens here into its dark heart — a space where the thorn-vines draw back from a central dais of compressed and hardened briar-matter, the surface worn smooth by something that sits here with regularity.  The dais is not natural: the vines have been trained and trimmed and killed and regrown in deliberate cycles over years until the resulting structure is as solid and as precisely shaped as worked stone.  @@pSerpentine patterns@@N run across its surface, cut into the hardened briar by something sharp and patient, and the purple-tinged air above the dais is noticeably thicker than the surrounding maze atmosphere — a visible column of slower air, as if the nexus creates its own weather.  From the dais, every channel in the surrounding maze can be felt, a proprioceptive awareness of all the briar's paths at once, which is not a comfortable thing to feel unless one belongs here.  The Briar Queen's seat radiates old power and older malice in the silence.~
