Two enormous trees here have grown into each other at their mid-sections, their trunks fusing over decades into a single unit that spans the path like an arch.  The arch is large enough to walk beneath without crouching, and the passage through it is clearly designated — the forest on both sides of the arch-path is impassably dense, routing everything through the living gate.  The bark of the fused section is entirely different from the surrounding trees: smooth, dark purple rather than the usual grey-black, and warm to the touch in a manner that suggests internal biological activity rather than absorbed heat.~
