#1076
The Bog Margin Forest~
The trees here show the effect of proximity to the Miasma Bog's toxic atmosphere — their lower bark is blackened by the accumulated condensation of bog-gas, their lower branches have died and the roots nearest the bog's edge have withdrawn upward from the saturated soil.  The ground is still forest floor here, but it is wet and unstable, each step producing a sucking sound and leaving a footprint that fills with dark water.  The transition zone between forest and bog is not a clean boundary but a gradual poisoning, the forest losing coherence as the bog wins.~
