The Watchpost Canopy Platform~
The rope-ladder from the ruined watchpost below terminates here, at a broad platform of ancient planking lashed to the confluence of four massive branches, sixty feet above the forest floor.  The platform is rotted but structurally sound — the wood has hardened with age into something denser and darker than the original timber, and the lashings holding it to the branches are so old they have partially grown into the bark.  From here, the Withered Depths spreads in every direction below, a solid dark canopy broken only by the faint bioluminescent glow of zones below.  The air up here is cleaner and colder than below, carrying wind that brings the smell of open sky mixed with the inevitable corruption.  Several rope bridges and vine-walkways lead outward from this platform into the canopy proper.~
