#1142
The Clear Spring~
A spring of clean water rises here, visible through the transparent shimmer of pure water over pale stone, welling up from a source deep in the earth and collecting in a small pool before flowing outward through the moss.  The water is cold and clear and tastes of minerals and nothing else — no sulphur, no iron, no fungal taint.  The pool is perhaps two feet deep and perfectly still except for the gentle welling at its centre.  Small aquatic creatures live in the pool: tiny translucent fish, water-insects, things that could not survive in any of the toxic water of the surrounding zones.  The spring's existence in the sanctum is either the cause of the corruption's inability to penetrate here, or the effect of that inability — in either case, its presence is precious.~
