#1143
The Ancient Oak~
An oak tree of extraordinary size stands at the centre of the Verdant Sanctum's eastern section, its trunk wider than any tree encountered in the zones behind, its bark covered in the same deeply cut spiral carvings as the druid circle stones in the bog.  The oak is alive — vibrantly, almost aggressively alive, its leaves so green they generate their own light, its sap pressure so high that it can be heard moving in the wood when the ambient sound is quiet enough.  The tree's presence has a physical quality: standing within a few feet of it causes a warmth, a steadying, a sense of something benevolent that has survived everything the blight has thrown at this forest and will continue to survive.  It is the source of the sanctum's preservation, or at least one of the sources.  The carvings on its bark match those of the druid circle to the north.~
