#1144
The Eastern Sanctum Edge~
The Verdant Sanctum's eastern limit is clearly marked — the green and living trees step back here at a precise boundary, and beyond it the Heartrot Grove's purple-dark begins immediately.  The boundary is maintained by something: at its line, the corruption of the grove meets resistance, the purple bioluminescence dimming at the line and going no further.  Looking along the boundary in both directions, the green-purple division holds, a straight-ish line maintained by will.  The guardian of this sanctum, whatever it is, has been holding this line for a very long time, and something about standing at the edge gives the strong impression that the guardian is aware of each breach, each approach, each threat.~
