#1147
The Spring Outflow Channel~
The water from the clear spring flows south through this section in an open channel it has carved through the moss over decades, the channel edges colonised by tiny aquatic plants that trail their roots in the current.  The channel is navigable on foot by stepping from one moss-bank to the other, and the sound of moving water is the dominant sound here — unusually loud in the sanctum's normal quiet, suggesting the channel amplifies or the water carries sound from its source above.  The guardian's influence is less strong here than at the clearing — the outskirts of the sanctum are less defended, as though the guardian concentrates its attention on the centre.~
