#1148
The Southern Oak Stand~
A group of younger oaks — younger being relative, they are still centuries old — stands in this southern section of the sanctum, forming a loose circle of their own that echoes the ancient oak's root circle to the north.  Each oak shows the same spiral carvings on its bark, though these are shallower, more recently cut, as if added in sequence over years.  The carvings in this stand tell a story if read in sequence from tree to tree, but the language of the story is the same undecipherable script as the druid circle stones.  Whatever is recorded here was recorded in a time before the corruption, when the druids who made this place still lived.~
