#1149
The Hidden Egress~
The very southern tip of the Verdant Sanctum ends here in a final cluster of trees whose roots, above ground, form a sheltered alcove.  The alcove is the most hidden point in the sanctum — invisible from any adjacent section until within a few feet, the root-walls screening it completely.  Within the alcove, the moss is undisturbed, suggesting almost nothing finds this place; the air is the cleanest in the entire Withered Depths.  On the western root-wall, scratched in the same script as the druid circle and the southern oaks but in a rough, recent hand, is a single sentence in a language that resolves, for anyone who has seen enough of the area's carving-language to recognise its patterns, into something that means approximately: The way back is always west.  A faint shimmer in the western root-wall — a thinning in the boundary of the sanctum that corresponds to the thinning of the boundary in the corrupted zone directly to the west — marks where the forest's own hidden path returns a traveller to the zone's entry.~
